## 8. Phase 2.6 deep-dive — Member-payout staging engine (backend half)

### 8.1 What changes vs today

Today, the **officer picks one payout method at the run level** — every member's interest goes to FOSA, or every member's dividend buys shares, etc. (`tenant_operations.default_interest_payout` is the default for the run; `interest_payout_method` enum on the run captures the choice.) That's fine for batch operations but doesn't match how modern SACCOs (Stima, Mwalimu, Tower, Unaitas) actually work today: each member sees their issued amount on a portal and chooses individually.

The architectural change in Phase 2.6: **add a `member_choice` payout method** that defers the decision to the member. Lines posted under that method don't immediately credit FOSA / buy shares / send M-PESA — instead they stage into a "payouts pending" balance the member can act on. The portal UI that surfaces these to members lives in **Phase 6 (Member Portal)**; Phase 2.6 ships the backend staging + claim endpoints + officer-side tools for forced credit / cancellation / preview.

### 8.2 The data model

```sql
-- New table: per-member payout balances awaiting their choice.
CREATE TABLE member_pending_payouts (
  id                  uuid PRIMARY KEY,
  tenant_id           uuid NOT NULL REFERENCES tenants(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  counterparty_id     uuid NOT NULL,
  source_run_id       uuid NOT NULL,                    -- interest_runs.id or dividend_runs.id
  source_kind         text NOT NULL CHECK (source_kind IN ('interest','dividend')),
  source_line_id      uuid NOT NULL,                    -- pointer back to the run line
  gross_amount        numeric(18,2) NOT NULL,
  wht_amount          numeric(18,2) NOT NULL,
  net_amount          numeric(18,2) NOT NULL,
  staged_at           timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  expires_at          timestamptz,                       -- when "claim window" closes
  status              text NOT NULL DEFAULT 'available'
    CHECK (status IN ('available','claimed','expired','force_credited','reversed')),
  claimed_at          timestamptz,
  claimed_method      text,                              -- 'fosa_credit' | 'buy_shares' | 'mpesa_b2c' | 'bank_transfer'
  claim_destination   text,                              -- account_no, msisdn, etc.
  posted_txn_id       uuid,
  UNIQUE (source_line_id)
);
```

When an interest or dividend run is posted with `payout_method = member_choice`, the per-member lines insert `member_pending_payouts` rows in `available` status instead of immediately crediting the destination.

### 8.3 The member-side action

On the portal:

- **Payouts page** (`/portal/payouts`): table of available pending payouts. Per row: source (Interest Run 2026 / Dividend Run 2026), staged date, expiry, gross, WHT, net, claim button.
- **Claim modal** per row:
  - Net amount (read-only)
  - Method picker: ◯ Credit to my FOSA  ◯ Buy more shares  ◯ Send to my M-PESA  ◯ Send to my bank account on file
  - Destination details (auto-filled from the member's on-file MSISDN / bank; editable subject to KYC re-verification for large amounts)
  - OTP confirmation (always — these are real-money actions)
  - Submit → fires immediately
- **Bulk claim**: "Claim all to FOSA" / "Claim all to M-PESA" — checkbox-driven multi-action with one OTP.

### 8.4 The officer-side controls

- **Per-tenant policy** in Settings → Operations:
  - `member_payout_window_days` (default 180) — after this, unclaimed payouts flip to `force_credited` (officer auto-credits to FOSA so members don't lose access).
  - `member_payout_max_per_day_kes` (default 50,000) — cap per member per day. Excess requires officer approval.
  - `member_payout_requires_approval_above_kes` (default 25,000) — over this, a workflow approval gate fires before posting.
  - `member_payout_methods text[]` — restrict which methods are allowed (e.g. some SACCOs want to disable bank_transfer self-service).
- **Force-credit batch**: officer can manually trigger force-credit-to-FOSA on a member's pending payouts (e.g. dormant member who'll never log in).
- **Cancellation**: officer can cancel a pending payout (with reason) — flips to `reversed`, no GL impact.

### 8.5 GL posting timing

When does the JE land?

**Option A — at run-post time, lands in a clearing account.** When the run posts with `member_choice`, the JE is:
- DR Interest Expense (5000) / CR Member Payouts Clearing (2520) [new GL code]
- DR Member Payouts Clearing (2520) / CR WHT Payable (2530)

Then when the member claims, the clearing account is debited and the destination credited:
- For FOSA credit: DR 2520 / CR Member Savings (2000)
- For buy shares: DR 2520 / CR Member Share Capital (3000)
- For M-PESA: DR 2520 / CR M-PESA Cash (1030)

The clearing account balance equals total staged payouts — auditable, reconcilable, simple.

**Option B — at claim time only.** The run-post JE only covers the WHT; the rest defers. Cleaner on the books but the member's net amount isn't an asset of theirs until they claim — odd accounting position.

**Recommendation: A.** The member's net amount IS theirs from run-post time; staging in a clearing account is the right accounting recognition.

### 8.6 Hard dependency on member portal

This phase **requires a working member portal**. Today there isn't one — it's planned as Phase 6 of the Loans work. Two options:

- **Defer Phase 2.6 until Loans Phase 6 lands.** Easiest. Loans Phase 6 builds the full member portal (login, dashboard, loan calculator, statement, apply, guarantor responses, PTPs). Adding the payouts page is one more page on the same shell.
- **Build a minimal member portal slice for payouts only**, ahead of Loans Phase 6. New module `web/member/` with just login + payouts page. Then Loans Phase 6 fills in the rest of the portal pages. **Faster path** if members getting payout self-service is more urgent than the loan-portal features.

